parameters: There's a door, it is unlocked but there are sounds coming from within.
Door is locked, it looks like it hasn't been used in ages.
Perhaps there's a key for it in another room.
A long abandoned minecart, the wheels fail to turn due to rust.
This large gate is locked but it needs a special key to unlock. Perhaps it's somewhere in here.
With a loud bang, the lock released.
There's a hole with pure energy flowing forth. If you reach in, you may gain untold amounts of power.
Strength to destroy any enemy in your path and save your friends.
Do you want to reach in and accept this power?
You can't believe your eyes. It's real. Your veins glow as it travels through you.
With a breath of fresh air..... you....
The door won't budge. You notice a small mechanism beside the door with numbers
below a carved skull and bones. Perhaps it depicts how many monsters
The number rests at \V[23] while the number 5 is colored bright green.
The moment you stepped up to the door, the number slid to match \V[23] kills.
Suddenly you heard the locking mechanism release.
I have a bad feeling about this, \N[1].
Yeah.... me too. It'll be okay though. We've got this.
How are you always so sure about these things?
We're strong people and no matter what we face, we'll get through it.
This would run a scene and teleport you to the forest town.
None of that is scripted at this moment but I'll send you
back to the forest town because you'll be stuck here if I didn't.
Come back in later versions to get the full experience! Bye!
This gate is where the portal ends up, but it's not scripted yet either.
Anyhow, away you go. Have fun!
Your party lies on the floor, barely clinging to life. Distorted voices surround you.
Everything fades as you're being dragged away.
You awake feeling somewhat refreshed. You're lucky to be alive.
You feel energy pulling your hand to the statue.
Do you want to reach out and touch it?
The statue accepted you and blessed your party, recovering health and removing all ailments.
You feel its power fading away.
